 Here's what to run on RunPod:

  Full sweep (all 7 datasets, GPU config):
  cd macro-ad && python sweep.py --root_path ../dataset --config configs/gpu_sweep.json --gpu cuda

  Single dataset test:
  cd macro-ad && python run.py --config configs/gpu_sweep.json --data MSL --root_path ../dataset --mode train_test --gpu cuda && python evaluate.py --data MSL --root_path ../dataset

  Conservative sweep (default config, just GPU acceleration):
  cd macro-ad && python sweep.py --root_path ../dataset --config configs/default.json --gpu cuda